1
00:00:01,450 --> 00:00:21,450
http://hiqve.com/

2
00:00:27,569 --> 00:00:28,903
Where are you going?

3
00:02:01,789 --> 00:02:04,707
This isn't yellow fever. This is smallpox.

4
00:02:04,792 --> 00:02:06,834
I know.

5
00:02:06,919 --> 00:02:11,088
And you didn't think this was important
information for me to have?

6
00:02:11,173 --> 00:02:13,007
Yellow fever is common.

7
00:02:14,426 --> 00:02:16,886
Rest of the world would not even notice.

8
00:02:16,970 --> 00:02:18,721
But smallpox,

9
00:02:18,806 --> 00:02:22,266
would you buy beef or coffee beans
from a country with that?

10
00:02:23,060 --> 00:02:26,979
But I could have brought the vaccine.
Medicines.

11
00:02:27,064 --> 00:02:29,398
I'm equipped for the wrong disease.

12
00:02:31,360 --> 00:02:33,778
You will do as you're told.

13
00:02:33,862 --> 00:02:37,740
After all, it was your country that
caused this outbreak in the first place.

14
00:03:00,264 --> 00:03:01,931
Are you American?

15
00:03:03,267 --> 00:03:06,060
Help me. Help me.

16
00:03:13,819 --> 00:03:15,444
John Thackery, Philadelphia.

17
00:03:15,529 --> 00:03:17,238
August Robertson, New York.

18
00:03:17,322 --> 00:03:18,865
I know the name.

19
00:03:18,949 --> 00:03:20,533
What are you doing here?

20
00:03:20,617 --> 00:03:22,326
I'm a doctor.

21
00:03:22,411 --> 00:03:26,038
I was working the Mosquito Coast.
They called me in for this.

22
00:03:26,123 --> 00:03:29,667
This is the last place I expected to
see a man from the society pages.

23
00:03:29,751 --> 00:03:32,086
My shipping company,
they use Nicaragua as a shortcut

24
00:03:32,170 --> 00:03:34,130
to the West Coast and the Orient and back.

25
00:03:34,214 --> 00:03:36,382
Two weeks crossing this country
saves me two months

26
00:03:36,466 --> 00:03:39,385
in navigation around South America.

27
00:03:39,469 --> 00:03:41,888
So why are they keeping you prisoner?

28
00:03:41,972 --> 00:03:45,224
Are you the American that's supposed to have
caused this outbreak?

29
00:03:45,309 --> 00:03:47,727
My shipping company pays them
in trinkets and blankets

30
00:03:47,811 --> 00:03:50,062
and now they're saying
those blankets made them sick.

31
00:03:50,147 --> 00:03:52,315
That's very possible.

32
00:03:52,399 --> 00:03:55,401
- They killed 12 of my men. Mostly Hondurans.
- Hey! Hey!

33
00:03:55,485 --> 00:03:57,153
And they're gonna kill me, I can assure you.

34
00:03:57,237 --> 00:03:59,238
Please, you've got to help me.

35
00:03:59,406 --> 00:04:00,865
You need to let the American go.

36
00:04:01,825 --> 00:04:04,327
He will pay for this disease with his life.

37
00:04:04,411 --> 00:04:06,829
But you can't be sure he's responsible.

38
00:04:06,914 --> 00:04:07,997
He stays.

39
00:04:10,125 --> 00:04:13,210
Well, then I won't cure these people.

40
00:04:13,295 --> 00:04:15,630
Then you will end up
like your American friend.

41
00:04:16,506 --> 00:04:19,926
If this thing spreads,
it's the most contagious thing on the Earth.

42
00:04:20,177 --> 00:04:23,054
You let him go, I will save these people.

43
00:04:29,227 --> 00:04:30,353
Without the vaccine?

44
00:04:31,688 --> 00:04:33,689
I have a way.

45
00:05:19,194 --> 00:05:20,903
These are the survivors.

46
00:05:21,446 --> 00:05:25,074
They can no longer get the disease.
They're immune.

47
00:05:25,158 --> 00:05:27,827
So they can help us
with those who still have it.

48
00:05:27,911 --> 00:05:31,414
Tell them to wrap these
bandages around the skin.

49
00:05:31,748 --> 00:05:34,291
It will help their sores heal.

50
00:05:55,522 --> 00:05:59,358
For those who haven't gotten the disease,
this will keep them safe.

51
00:05:59,443 --> 00:06:01,360
They'll get a mild case of it.

52
00:06:01,445 --> 00:06:05,656
They'll definitely recover
and they'll never get it again.

53
00:06:05,741 --> 00:06:09,493
Even if this does work,
I'm still keeping his cargo.

54
00:06:58,293 --> 00:07:00,336
Girls, you ready?

55
00:08:07,195 --> 00:08:09,530
Good morning, Dr. Gallinger.

56
00:08:13,451 --> 00:08:17,496
Detective, what can I do for you?

57
00:08:17,581 --> 00:08:21,208
I had some more information
regarding Dr. Cotton's death

58
00:08:21,293 --> 00:08:23,335
that you might be interested in hearing

59
00:08:23,420 --> 00:08:26,881
since, as you said, you and your wife
were so fond of him.

60
00:08:29,259 --> 00:08:31,302
Uh, would you follow me?

61
00:08:34,598 --> 00:08:36,223
What is it?

62
00:08:36,349 --> 00:08:39,727
We've confirmed that he was
most definitely poisoned.

63
00:08:40,979 --> 00:08:43,898
And we now know who did it.

64
00:08:46,067 --> 00:08:47,484
You do?

65
00:08:48,028 --> 00:08:50,654
You might want to prepare yourself.

66
00:08:52,407 --> 00:08:54,158
It was his sons who did him in.

67
00:08:54,659 --> 00:08:56,368
They both were studying at Princeton,

68
00:08:56,453 --> 00:09:00,122
were slowly adding arsenic
to their father's meals over time.

69
00:09:03,627 --> 00:09:05,252
You're positive about this?

70
00:09:05,337 --> 00:09:06,879
They confessed it.

71
00:09:06,963 --> 00:09:08,839
They were surprised that he'd died so quickly

72
00:09:08,924 --> 00:09:12,468
since, as they said, they had
only been adding the arsenic a short while.

73
00:09:13,053 --> 00:09:16,972
Must have given him more than they realized.
Not that I blame them.

74
00:09:17,057 --> 00:09:19,850
From what I gather, the old man was a nut.

75
00:09:21,561 --> 00:09:25,522
You know, that crazy man
pulled the teeth out of their head.

76
00:09:27,651 --> 00:09:29,985
His own children's teeth.

77
00:09:30,070 --> 00:09:32,363
Why the hell do you do something like that?

78
00:09:34,824 --> 00:09:37,117
He thought it would keep them sane.

79
00:09:39,663 --> 00:09:41,956
Have the boys been arrested?

80
00:09:42,540 --> 00:09:45,125
They killed themselves before we could.

81
00:09:45,210 --> 00:09:48,671
So I guess Daddy's treatment
didn't work out so great.

82
00:09:50,257 --> 00:09:52,883
Anyway, just thought you'd want to know.

83
00:09:53,385 --> 00:09:54,677
Ah. Thank you.

84
00:09:55,470 --> 00:09:57,346
How's your wife?

85
00:09:59,307 --> 00:10:00,432
Doing well.

86
00:10:01,059 --> 00:10:03,018
Give her my best.

87
00:10:23,456 --> 00:10:25,708
Will you excuse us for a moment, Dudley?

88
00:10:27,711 --> 00:10:28,794
Thank you.

89
00:10:31,381 --> 00:10:33,382
Your mother said you're leaving.

90
00:10:34,509 --> 00:10:38,929
Going to Ohio tonight.
The refinery is nearly ready.

91
00:10:39,014 --> 00:10:41,098
Talking with some men in Cleveland
and up near Detroit

92
00:10:41,182 --> 00:10:43,726
about using our gasoline
for automotive propulsion.

93
00:10:44,519 --> 00:10:46,562
Well, when will you be back?

94
00:10:48,356 --> 00:10:50,065
Do you really care?

95
00:10:50,775 --> 00:10:51,984
Of course.

96
00:10:52,068 --> 00:10:53,902
'Cause I want you to come with me.

97
00:10:54,612 --> 00:10:56,655
It's a part of my father's business
that could be mine.

98
00:10:56,740 --> 00:10:59,616
I can build it. We can make a life there.

99
00:11:00,327 --> 00:11:04,997
Phillip, it's a lot all at once.
I need some time.

100
00:11:05,081 --> 00:11:10,669
No, I don't want words or protestations.
It's not what you say, it's what you do.

101
00:11:10,754 --> 00:11:14,006
I'm leaving tonight.
I don't know when I'll be back.

102
00:11:14,090 --> 00:11:16,175
Now either you're coming
with me, your husband,

103
00:11:16,259 --> 00:11:19,428
to be with me wherever we end up,
or you're not.

104
00:11:19,971 --> 00:11:23,766
And if you're not,
I'll find someone who wants to.

105
00:11:24,726 --> 00:11:26,727
I deserve at least that.

106
00:11:42,911 --> 00:11:44,620
May I come in?

107
00:11:53,671 --> 00:11:55,589
How are you doing?

108
00:12:00,970 --> 00:12:05,307
I'm deeply sorry, John.

109
00:12:08,019 --> 00:12:09,770
What did you want?

110
00:12:11,815 --> 00:12:14,566
Just wanted to give you
a report on the twins.

111
00:12:14,651 --> 00:12:17,486
Some good news for a change.

112
00:12:19,155 --> 00:12:21,782
Dr. Chickering and I
examined them this morning.

113
00:12:21,866 --> 00:12:23,951
Nika's pneumonia has receded.

114
00:12:25,829 --> 00:12:29,081
The amount of albumin
in their urine has decreased.

115
00:12:29,165 --> 00:12:32,209
They're eating full meals and

116
00:12:32,544 --> 00:12:34,670
they took their first steps alone.

117
00:12:37,340 --> 00:12:38,674
Also, the orphanage informs me

118
00:12:38,758 --> 00:12:41,093
that a family from Missouri
has agreed to take the girls.

119
00:12:41,177 --> 00:12:42,761
They arrived in the city yesterday

120
00:12:42,846 --> 00:12:46,181
and are just waiting on
our approval to let them go.

121
00:12:46,724 --> 00:12:48,434
I think they're ready.

122
00:12:49,602 --> 00:12:51,478
Sounds like it.

123
00:12:55,024 --> 00:12:56,024
Congratulations.

124
00:13:32,604 --> 00:13:35,439
So, here's what I'm thinking.

125
00:13:35,857 --> 00:13:38,942
We start at the East Side piers.

126
00:13:39,027 --> 00:13:41,361
Find some sailors coming back
from a long time at sea

127
00:13:41,446 --> 00:13:42,988
looking to get their logs dunked.

128
00:13:43,072 --> 00:13:45,532
Then we head to 29th Street.

129
00:13:45,617 --> 00:13:49,578
They've got enough brothels and dance halls
to keep us selling till Christmas.

130
00:13:49,829 --> 00:13:50,871
Fine.

131
00:13:53,416 --> 00:13:56,001
How long you gonna be sore with me?

132
00:13:56,461 --> 00:13:58,337
As long as I feel like.

133
00:13:58,421 --> 00:14:00,923
I may not be a nun anymore,
but I took my vows,

134
00:14:01,007 --> 00:14:03,258
vows that you know I intend on keeping.

135
00:14:03,468 --> 00:14:07,387
It was one little kiss, all right?
A kiss I didn't even get.

136
00:14:07,472 --> 00:14:11,058
You're a hound,
like all them fellas getting off the boats

137
00:14:11,142 --> 00:14:13,268
looking to get their logs dunked.

138
00:14:13,353 --> 00:14:16,522
I can't trust you now,
just like I shouldn't have all this time.

139
00:14:17,649 --> 00:14:19,525
I got carried away is all.

140
00:14:21,277 --> 00:14:23,111
Because what I said is true.

141
00:14:25,281 --> 00:14:26,782
I do have feelings for you.

142
00:14:30,703 --> 00:14:33,413
Then I'd ask you to please
keep them to yourself.

143
00:14:35,166 --> 00:14:36,750
This box is ready.

144
00:14:38,294 --> 00:14:41,088
Guess those vows
didn't include one of forgiveness.

145
00:14:41,172 --> 00:14:42,172
What?

146
00:14:42,257 --> 00:14:43,840
Nothing, all right? I'm sorry.

147
00:14:43,925 --> 00:14:46,468
I didn't mean to tempt you
into breaking your vows.

148
00:14:46,803 --> 00:14:51,223
Believe me, a gorilla like you,
there wasn't the least bit of temptation.

149
00:15:07,073 --> 00:15:08,115
Mr. Jenkins.

150
00:15:09,075 --> 00:15:11,076
- Herman Barrow.
- Good to meet you, Mr. Barrow.

151
00:15:11,160 --> 00:15:12,828
And you, sir.

152
00:15:13,162 --> 00:15:14,496
- Shall we?
- Yes.

153
00:15:28,803 --> 00:15:32,264
Thank you, Mr. Barrow.
Welcome to the Metropolitan Club.

154
00:15:48,781 --> 00:15:52,701
I don't know what a Vander is,
but I'm sho glad he done built it.

155
00:15:52,994 --> 00:15:55,412
Herman, how are you?

156
00:15:55,496 --> 00:15:57,289
I'm very well, Corky, thank you.

157
00:15:57,373 --> 00:16:00,375
That was a wonderful evening. Please.

158
00:16:00,710 --> 00:16:01,710
Oh.

159
00:16:03,463 --> 00:16:06,465
Well, we very much appreciated
your generous donation.

160
00:16:19,228 --> 00:16:20,729
Dr. Thackery?

161
00:16:22,565 --> 00:16:25,442
Dr. Thackery, it's Nurse Baker.

162
00:16:26,319 --> 00:16:28,820
The twins are leaving.
I thought you'd want to know.

163
00:16:49,384 --> 00:16:53,595
Where is Dr. Thackery?
We want to say goodbye.

164
00:16:53,680 --> 00:16:58,934
I'm sure he wishes he could be here,
but unfortunately he's elsewhere.

165
00:17:03,398 --> 00:17:05,023
Be well, girls.

166
00:17:13,866 --> 00:17:15,617
Finally, a good outcome.

167
00:17:19,288 --> 00:17:24,459
Well, I don't suppose he's rushing over
for one last wave at the twins.

168
00:17:24,794 --> 00:17:26,670
You brought me up on charges?

169
00:17:26,754 --> 00:17:27,796
What?

170
00:17:27,880 --> 00:17:31,216
I've been called to defend myself
in front of the state medical board.

171
00:17:31,634 --> 00:17:33,260
You sterilized idiots?

172
00:17:33,344 --> 00:17:34,845
Dozens.

173
00:17:34,929 --> 00:17:37,472
I had no idea how far outside

174
00:17:37,557 --> 00:17:39,349
the brotherhood of physicians
you were until now.

175
00:17:39,434 --> 00:17:43,437
And I had no idea how far outside you were
until you sabotaged me.

176
00:17:43,521 --> 00:17:44,855
How?

177
00:17:45,690 --> 00:17:49,025
The Carr surgery. I know it was you.

178
00:17:49,110 --> 00:17:51,194
Why? Because there's no chance
you would ever make a mistake?

179
00:17:51,279 --> 00:17:54,406
No, because there is no chance that
you are a better doctor than I am.

180
00:17:54,741 --> 00:17:57,242
Oh, for God's sake. Shut up, both of you.

181
00:17:57,952 --> 00:17:59,953
Everett, you're supposed to be on the ward.

182
00:18:02,331 --> 00:18:04,875
Have I missed the twins?

183
00:18:05,209 --> 00:18:07,753
Just. They asked after you.

184
00:18:09,964 --> 00:18:11,423
Thack! Thack!

185
00:18:11,507 --> 00:18:13,341
Quick, quick, fetch a gurney.

186
00:18:13,426 --> 00:18:14,426
No.

187
00:18:14,510 --> 00:18:16,803
You have been in pain for weeks.
You need to be examined.

188
00:18:16,888 --> 00:18:19,222
You mean opened up? Like hell.

189
00:18:19,849 --> 00:18:22,267
All right, well, maybe there's
another alternative.

190
00:19:01,140 --> 00:19:03,225
Have a look, doctors.

191
00:19:07,188 --> 00:19:08,730
My Lord.

192
00:19:09,982 --> 00:19:13,276
You do realize the patient is conscious,
don't you, Bertie?

193
00:19:14,570 --> 00:19:16,988
I was marveling at the technology.

194
00:19:18,324 --> 00:19:22,452
Zinberg taught you to tell the truth.
I taught you to lie.

195
00:19:23,120 --> 00:19:25,956
Seems like neither of us did a very good job.

196
00:19:26,833 --> 00:19:28,834
It is a marvelous invention.

197
00:19:28,918 --> 00:19:30,335
And what does it tell you?

198
00:19:30,419 --> 00:19:32,921
That a section of your bowel is ischemic.

199
00:19:33,506 --> 00:19:34,589
Agreed.

200
00:19:36,217 --> 00:19:38,051
I suppose we can guess what's caused it.

201
00:19:39,011 --> 00:19:40,303
Well, we don't need to get into that.

202
00:19:40,388 --> 00:19:42,097
No, that's all right.

203
00:19:42,807 --> 00:19:44,933
A man ingests cocaine for long enough,

204
00:19:45,017 --> 00:19:48,562
then his intestinal blood vessels
don't stand a chance.

205
00:19:50,273 --> 00:19:51,857
You'll need a resection.

206
00:19:52,859 --> 00:19:55,861
Is the entire intestine necrotic?

207
00:19:57,446 --> 00:19:59,948
Well, we can only guess
from what little we can see,

208
00:20:01,033 --> 00:20:02,742
but I'll schedule surgery
as soon as possible.

209
00:20:02,827 --> 00:20:06,162
No, I want to find an alternative.

210
00:20:06,747 --> 00:20:08,081
What do you mean?

211
00:20:08,708 --> 00:20:10,292
I don't want to rush into it.

212
00:20:12,086 --> 00:20:15,297
There are other things I want to try.

213
00:20:15,965 --> 00:20:18,925
- Medications.
- You collapsed on the street.

214
00:20:19,302 --> 00:20:21,469
Your bowel looks like the badlands.

215
00:20:21,554 --> 00:20:22,971
What more evidence do you need?

216
00:20:23,055 --> 00:20:24,848
No medication is gonna repair that.

217
00:20:24,932 --> 00:20:28,268
Yet it is not for any of you to decide.

218
00:20:29,478 --> 00:20:33,690
Ladies, I am kindly asking you
to please stay out of my way.

219
00:20:33,774 --> 00:20:35,984
I will go wherever I please.

220
00:20:36,527 --> 00:20:40,614
These nurses are saying
I am barred from the building.

221
00:20:41,616 --> 00:20:44,826
You need to make an appointment
like everyone else.

222
00:20:45,912 --> 00:20:47,871
I am not everyone else.

223
00:20:50,833 --> 00:20:53,793
Thank you, nurses. Everything is fine.

224
00:20:55,463 --> 00:20:57,464
Please close the door.

225
00:21:03,846 --> 00:21:06,473
How's your whore? Is she well?

226
00:21:07,099 --> 00:21:09,559
Junia is very well. Thank you.

227
00:21:10,853 --> 00:21:14,689
And how's your new apartment?
Tiny and awful, I trust?

228
00:21:15,316 --> 00:21:17,442
Actually, that's why I'm here.

229
00:21:17,526 --> 00:21:22,656
I want you to buy me a big,
nice one with a view like yours

230
00:21:22,740 --> 00:21:24,950
for me and the children.

231
00:21:25,034 --> 00:21:27,786
Preferably on the Upper East Side.

232
00:21:27,870 --> 00:21:30,580
In a dream, that might be
something I would do.

233
00:21:31,582 --> 00:21:33,917
By law, I owe you nothing.

234
00:21:47,056 --> 00:21:48,807
What is that?

235
00:21:48,891 --> 00:21:52,268
Apparently,
it's the actual amount of steel

236
00:21:52,353 --> 00:21:55,939
that was delivered to the new Knick
on March 4, 1901.

237
00:21:56,816 --> 00:21:58,817
I'm assuming that somewhere in this building

238
00:21:58,901 --> 00:22:02,529
is a document claiming that the delivery
was much greater,

239
00:22:02,613 --> 00:22:05,949
as was the amount that you required
the hospital to pay for it.

240
00:22:06,033 --> 00:22:08,994
We'll both just suppose
we know where the extra money went.

241
00:22:10,538 --> 00:22:11,913
Where did you get that?

242
00:22:11,998 --> 00:22:14,082
You keep
excellent records, Herman.

243
00:22:14,583 --> 00:22:16,626
And you were very smart to keep them
out of the hospital

244
00:22:16,711 --> 00:22:18,378
where people could find them.

245
00:22:19,046 --> 00:22:24,175
Unfortunately, when I went
to the bank the other day to retrieve jewelry

246
00:22:24,260 --> 00:22:26,594
from my safe-deposit box to sell it,

247
00:22:27,263 --> 00:22:32,392
the banker mistakenly gave me the keys
to the other Barrow box.

248
00:22:34,770 --> 00:22:36,896
Where are they now, the papers?

249
00:22:36,981 --> 00:22:38,898
In a new safe-deposit box.

250
00:22:40,151 --> 00:22:45,405
They're all there, everything you did
and every penny you stole.

251
00:22:48,743 --> 00:22:50,118
What do you want?

252
00:22:51,120 --> 00:22:54,164
I want to live the life
I was accustomed to living.

