with the brothels

505
00:41:02,335 --> 00:41:05,254
you've heard of something
called the Golden Lotus.

506
00:41:07,757 --> 00:41:10,092
While he was having sex,

507
00:41:10,176 --> 00:41:15,722
I stuck my foot in the mouth of an Oriental
and let him suck on it as he ejaculated.

508
00:41:18,226 --> 00:41:21,770
And he paid me $100 for the pleasure.

509
00:41:23,731 --> 00:41:25,357
More than once.

510
00:41:29,237 --> 00:41:32,531
I just wanted you to know everything
before you went.

511
00:41:36,828 --> 00:41:38,537
Bye, Daddy.

512
00:41:40,248 --> 00:41:42,249
Enjoy your trip.

513
00:42:38,264 --> 00:42:39,514
Dad?

514
00:42:47,273 --> 00:42:49,233
Dad?

515
00:42:49,317 --> 00:42:51,318
Are you here?

516
00:42:55,657 --> 00:42:59,409
Hey, there.
I didn't expect to see you here.

517
00:42:59,494 --> 00:43:02,329
Come on up. The view is wonderful.

518
00:43:14,133 --> 00:43:15,759
That's a long walk.

519
00:43:17,178 --> 00:43:19,096
There'll be an elevator soon.

520
00:43:19,180 --> 00:43:20,555
Where's Henry?

521
00:43:20,640 --> 00:43:21,974
He'll be here any moment.

522
00:43:22,058 --> 00:43:25,519
Good. What do you think?

523
00:43:27,480 --> 00:43:28,480
Hmm?

524
00:43:29,232 --> 00:43:31,233
Cold rooms.

525
00:43:32,443 --> 00:43:35,112
Light therapy patio up on the roof.

526
00:43:36,990 --> 00:43:38,699
Gonna be a marvel.

527
00:43:42,328 --> 00:43:44,288
This is it.

528
00:43:46,416 --> 00:43:48,375
This is my legacy.

529
00:43:51,045 --> 00:43:55,215
Long after I'm gone,
this is what people will remember me for.

530
00:43:57,719 --> 00:44:01,054
I'm not certain it's all
you'll be remembered for.

531
00:44:02,348 --> 00:44:06,977
Well, there'll be the shipping
and other endeavors, but this,

532
00:44:07,061 --> 00:44:11,064
this is going to save lives every day.

533
00:44:12,734 --> 00:44:18,447
Then why would you be so greedy and foolish
as to risk and hurt so many people?

534
00:44:21,075 --> 00:44:22,784
What do you mean?

535
00:44:22,869 --> 00:44:25,329
I know about it, Dad.

536
00:44:25,413 --> 00:44:30,334
I know about the inspectors
and the bribes and the ports.

537
00:44:30,418 --> 00:44:31,835
I know about it all.

538
00:44:31,919 --> 00:44:34,171
Cornelia, you're jabbering.
What are you talking...

539
00:44:34,255 --> 00:44:37,007
Inspector Bradley and
the Immigration Office at the docks.

540
00:44:37,342 --> 00:44:39,885
You've been bribing him and his men.

541
00:44:41,637 --> 00:44:44,056
Inspector Brad...

542
00:44:44,140 --> 00:44:46,683
Oh, Neely, there isn't a shipping man

543
00:44:46,768 --> 00:44:49,478
in New York who doesn't go out
and slip those fellas

544
00:44:49,562 --> 00:44:53,607
a 20 every now and again to get
a little happy in a pub.

545
00:44:55,109 --> 00:44:56,985
But that is hardly a crime.

546
00:44:57,070 --> 00:45:02,282
If only that was your crime, but it's not.
I know it and Henry knows it.

547
00:45:03,326 --> 00:45:06,286
You move up the sick and the poor
to second-class,

548
00:45:06,371 --> 00:45:09,039
and the inspectors let them into the country

549
00:45:09,123 --> 00:45:12,000
where they infest the tenements
and the neighborhoods.

550
00:45:12,085 --> 00:45:15,212
People died, Dad. Lots of them.

551
00:45:15,296 --> 00:45:19,466
In San Francisco and Hawaii.
Here in New York.

552
00:45:19,550 --> 00:45:22,010
Speight found out and you killed him, too.

553
00:45:22,095 --> 00:45:23,553
What?

554
00:45:25,515 --> 00:45:29,976
What in the hell are you accusing me of?

555
00:45:30,061 --> 00:45:31,895
Don't make it worse by denying it.

556
00:45:31,979 --> 00:45:33,230
Neely, this is ridiculous.

557
00:45:33,314 --> 00:45:35,565
Don't touch me.

558
00:45:40,863 --> 00:45:42,489
I assure you

559
00:45:44,659 --> 00:45:48,370
I did none of the things that you say.

560
00:45:49,872 --> 00:45:53,875
Look around you. Take a good look around!

561
00:45:56,379 --> 00:46:00,340
If I was so concerned about money

562
00:46:01,801 --> 00:46:04,344
would I be working so hard
to give it away to the Knick?

563
00:46:04,429 --> 00:46:07,139
- I know your business is in trouble.
- What?

564
00:46:07,223 --> 00:46:10,308
- You owe Hobart an enormous amount.
- Neely!

565
00:46:13,479 --> 00:46:14,771
In a way.

566
00:46:15,940 --> 00:46:19,860
But that is just an investment
that he made in me.

567
00:46:20,528 --> 00:46:21,695
I am on the rebound.

568
00:46:21,779 --> 00:46:24,698
Yet you still can't cover
your commitments to the Knick.

569
00:46:26,492 --> 00:46:31,329
I did not do what you think.

570
00:46:31,956 --> 00:46:35,709
We're going to the police, Henry and I.

571
00:46:35,793 --> 00:46:37,544
It's already decided.

572
00:46:38,171 --> 00:46:40,964
Neely, this is preposterous.

573
00:46:45,553 --> 00:46:47,179
Do you smell that?

574
00:46:47,263 --> 00:46:49,014
What?

575
00:46:50,892 --> 00:46:54,561
Oh, my God. We've got to get out of here.

576
00:47:00,359 --> 00:47:02,360
Oh, God.

577
00:47:06,199 --> 00:47:08,074
Look, over there.

578
00:47:14,165 --> 00:47:15,957
It's a 20-foot drop.

579
00:47:19,003 --> 00:47:20,754
Help me with this.

580
00:47:27,678 --> 00:47:30,805
I'm gonna lower this ladder down in the hole.

581
00:47:31,974 --> 00:47:34,476
Oh, wait. You've got to go sideways.

582
00:47:34,560 --> 00:47:36,394
Here, go up. Go up.

583
00:47:37,939 --> 00:47:39,606
I got it.

584
00:47:40,858 --> 00:47:43,693
- All right, here.
- It's not long enough.

585
00:47:43,778 --> 00:47:45,946
It'll carry you most of the way, maybe more.

586
00:47:46,030 --> 00:47:47,822
You can climb down, hang, and drop.

587
00:47:47,907 --> 00:47:49,866
- I'll hold it from up here.
- No.

588
00:47:49,951 --> 00:47:52,035
You have to, Neely. There's no other way.

589
00:47:52,119 --> 00:47:53,620
- And what about you?
- Go find help.

590
00:47:53,704 --> 00:47:57,082
There's a fire brigade two blocks down.
They've probably already seen the smoke.

591
00:47:57,166 --> 00:47:59,042
I'll go up the stairs and
wait it out up there.

592
00:47:59,126 --> 00:48:00,377
- Now, go. You've got to go.
- I won't.

593
00:48:00,461 --> 00:48:05,131
Neely, you're running out of time!
Go! Get on this ladder and go now.

594
00:48:06,926 --> 00:48:10,387
That's it. Climb down as far as you can.

595
00:48:10,471 --> 00:48:13,723
Oh, God.

596
00:48:13,808 --> 00:48:16,017
That's it, Neely. Go.

597
00:48:16,102 --> 00:48:18,144
As far as you can go.

598
00:48:20,523 --> 00:48:22,148
That's it.

599
00:48:24,110 --> 00:48:25,819
Good, now let go.

600
00:48:25,903 --> 00:48:28,154
Now, Neely. Now!

601
00:48:34,495 --> 00:48:37,038
Neely? Neely?

602
00:48:37,123 --> 00:48:39,332
Neely, are you all right?

603
00:48:40,543 --> 00:48:42,377
Go get help.

604
00:48:42,461 --> 00:48:44,838
Go.

605
00:48:44,922 --> 00:48:46,631
Now.

606
00:49:17,872 --> 00:49:19,205
Where?

607
00:49:22,418 --> 00:49:24,002
Dad!

608
00:49:31,969 --> 00:49:33,803
No! No!

609
00:50:12,677 --> 00:50:14,761
Oh, God.

610
00:50:23,729 --> 00:50:26,022
Oh, God.

611
00:50:31,612 --> 00:50:33,279
We're almost there.

612
00:50:33,364 --> 00:50:35,907
We should talk
about compensation.

613
00:50:35,991 --> 00:50:39,452
No, I'm not much
interested in money.

614
00:50:41,872 --> 00:50:46,126
You know,
I fund a hospital in New York.

615
00:50:46,210 --> 00:50:48,336
The Knickerbocker.

616
00:50:48,421 --> 00:50:51,131
Isn't that where J.M. Christiansen is?

617
00:50:52,216 --> 00:50:54,634
I hear he's doing some astonishing work.

618
00:50:57,138 --> 00:51:00,557
You two should meet. I'll introduce you.

